From d1c95775ea76294191091ea219b36e282ecc2d7a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 11:42:22 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8: stream Anthropic responses + robust partial-JSON
 parser

Two related changes:

1. Streaming. IKrtAiClient gains postMessagesStream(requestId,
   request) and an onStreamEvent emitter. Main flips stream:true,
   parses Anthropic SSE events (message_start, content_block_delta,
   message_delta), and emits text deltas plus running token usage
   correlated by requestId. The renderer's TourGenerator now
   invokes the streaming endpoint, accumulates the response, and
   exposes an onUpdate callback that fires each time a new
   chapter completes inside the partial JSON. The PR pane wires
   onUpdate to tourState so chapters appear progressively in the
   Tour rail / Reading view / Storyboard graph as the model
   produces them.

2. Robust JSON extraction. The brittle 'first { ... last }' fallback
   is replaced with a brace-balanced scanner that walks the
   chapters array element-by-element, respecting strings and
   escapes. It returns whatever complete chapter objects it
   finds, so:
     - prose before/after the JSON no longer breaks parsing
     - opening fences without closing fences (truncated /
       streaming responses) still yield chapters
     - a partial last object simply stops the scan instead of
       blowing up the whole response

   The same scanner powers parseChaptersStreaming(text, files),
   which the streaming pipeline calls on every text delta to
   pull out completed chapters incrementally.
